#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:12
msgid "Brush panel."
msgstr "Panneau Brush."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:14
msgid ""
"Painting needs paint brushes and Blender provides a Brush Panel within "
"the Tool Shelf when it operates in *Weight Paint Mode*."
msgstr ""
"La peinture nécessite des brosses et Blender fournit un panneau *Brush* "
"dans le *Tool Shelf* quand il opère en *Mode Weight Paint*."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:18
msgid ""
"In the :ref:`Data-Block menu <ui-data-block>` you find predefined Brush "
"Presets. And you can create your own custom presets as needed."
msgstr ""
"Dans le :ref:`menu Data-Block <ui-data-block>` vous trouverez des "
"préréglages de brosse prédéfinis. Et vous pouvez créer vos propres "
"préréglages personnalisés au besoin."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:25
msgid "Weight :kbd:`W`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:21
msgid ""
"The weight (color) to be used by the brush. However, the weight value is "
"applied to the Vertex Group in different ways depending on the selected "
"Brush Blending mode (see below)."
msgstr ""
"Le poids (couleur) à utiliser par la brosse. Cependant, la valeur de "
"poids est appliquée au groupe de sommets de différentes manières selon le"
" mode *Brush Blending* sélectionné (voir ci-dessous)."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:25
msgid ""
"Use :kbd:`Ctrl-LMB` to sample the weight value of clicked vertex. :kbd"
":`Shift-LMB` lets you select the group from which to sample from."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:28
msgid "Strength"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:28
msgid ""
"This is the amount of paint to be applied per brush stroke. What that "
"means exactly also depends on the Brush Blending mode."
msgstr ""
"C'est la quantité de peinture à appliquer par coup de brosse. Ce que cela"
" signifie exactement dépend aussi du mode *Brush Blending*."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:31
msgid "Radius"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:31
msgid "The radius defines the area of influence of the brush."
msgstr "Le rayon définit la zone d'influence de la brosse."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:73
msgid "Blend mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:34
msgid ""
"The brush Blending mode defines in which way the weight value is applied "
"to the Vertex Group while painting."
msgstr ""
"Le *Blending mode* de la brosse définit de quelle manière la valeur de "
"poids est appliquée au groupe de sommets pendant la peinture. "

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:40
msgid "Mix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:37
msgid ""
"In this Blending mode the Weight value defines the *target weight* that "
"will eventually be reached when you paint long enough on the same "
"location of the mesh. And the strength determines how many strokes you "
"need to arrive at the target weight. Note that for strength = 1.0 the "
"target weight is painted immediately, and for Weight = 0.0 the brush just"
" does nothing."
msgstr ""
"Dans ce *Blending mode* la valeur *Weight* définit le *poids cible* qui "
"sera effectivement atteinte quand vous peignez assez longtemps à la même "
"position du maillage. Et la force (*strength*) détermine le nombre de "
"traits nécessaires pour arriver au poids cible. Notez que pour un "
"strength = 1.0 le poids cible est peint immédiatement, et pour un Weight "
"=0.0 la brosse ne fait rien. "

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:44
msgid "Add"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:43
msgid ""
"In this Blending mode the specified weight value is *added* to the vertex"
" weights. The strength determines which fraction of the weight gets added"
" per stroke. However, the brush will not paint weight values above 1.0."
msgstr ""
"Dans ce *Blending mode* la valeur de poids spécifiée est *ajoutée* aux "
"poids des sommets. La force (*strength*) détermine la fraction du poids à"
" ajouter par trait. Cependant, la brosse ne peindra pas les valeurs de "
"poids au dessus de 1.0."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:48
msgid "Subtract"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:47
msgid ""
"In this Blending mode the specified weight value is *subtracted* from the"
" vertex weights. The strength determines which fraction of the weight "
"gets removed per stroke. However, the brush will not paint weight values "
"below 0.0."
msgstr ""
"Dans ce *Blending mode* la valeur de poids spécifiée est *soustraite* aux"
" poids des sommets. La force (*strength*) détermine la fraction du poids "
"à supprimer par trait. Cependant, la brosse ne peindra pas les valeurs de"
" poids au dessous de 0.0."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:53
msgid "Lighten"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:51
msgid ""
"In this Blending mode the specified weight value is interpreted as the "
"target weight. Very similar to the Mix Blending mode, but only weights "
"below the target weight are affected. Weights above the target weight "
"remain unchanged."
msgstr ""
"Dans ce *Blending mode* la valeur de poids spécifiée est interprétée "
"comme le poids cible. Très similaire au *Blending mode* Mix, Mais seules "
"les poids inférieurs au poids cible sont affectés. Les poids supérieurs "
"au poids cible restent inchangés. "

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:57
msgid "Darken"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:56
msgid ""
"This Blending mode is very similar to the Lighten Blending mode. But only"
" weights above the target weight are affected. Weights below the target "
"weight remain unchanged."
msgstr ""
"Ce *Blending mode* est très similaire au *Blending mode* Lighten. Mais "
"seules les poids supérieurs au poids de la cible sont affectés. Les poids"
" inférieurs au poids de la cible restent inchangés. "

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:60
msgid "Multiply"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:60
msgid ""
"Multiplies the vertex weights with the specified weight value. This is "
"somewhat like subtract, but the amount of removed weight is now dependent"
" on the Weight value itself."
msgstr ""
"Multiplie les poids des sommets par la valeur de poids spécifiée. C'est "
"en quelque sorte une soustraction, mais la quantité de poids supprimée "
"est maintenant dépendante de la valeur de poids elle-même."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:73
msgid "Blur"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:63
msgid ""
"Smooths out the weighting of adjacent vertices. In this mode the Weight "
"Value is ignored. The strength defines how much the smoothing is applied."
msgstr ""
"Lisse le poids des sommets adjacents. Dans ce mode la valeur de poids est"
" ignorée. La force définit le niveau de lissage appliqué."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:73
msgid "Accumulate"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:68
msgid "This option keeps applying smoothing on top of the previous result."
msgstr ""
"Cette option conserve le lissage appliqué par dessus le résultat "
"précédent."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:72
msgid "Disable when painting individual vertices on lower poly modules."
msgstr ""
"Désactivez cette option pendant la peinture des sommets individuels sur "
"des modules faiblement polyédriques."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:73
msgid ""
"Enable for more dense geometry, or when you want to increase the blur "
"effect."
msgstr ""
"Activez cette option pour une géométrie plus dense, ou quand vous voulez "
"augmenter l'effet de flou."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:82
msgid "Auto Normalize"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:76
msgid ""
"Ensures that all deforming vertex groups add up to one while painting. "
"When this option is turned off, then all weights of a vertex can have any"
" value between 0.0 and 1.0. However, when Vertex Groups are used as "
"Deform Groups for character animation then Blender always interprets the "
"weight values relative to each other. That is, Blender always does a "
"normalization over all deform bones. Hence in practice it is not "
"necessary to maintain a strict normalization and further normalizing "
"weights should not affect animation at all."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:82
msgid ""
"This option works most intuitively when used to maintain normalization "
"while painting on top of weights that are already normalized with some "
"other tool."
msgstr ""
"Cette option fonctionne très intuitivement quand elle est utilisée pour "
"maintenir la normalisation pendant la peinture sur les poids qui sont "
"déjà normalisés avec un autre outil."

#: ../../<generated>:1
msgid "Multi-Paint"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:85
msgid ""
"Paint on all selected Vertex Groups simultaneously, in a way that "
"preserves their relative influence. This can be useful when tweaking "
"weights in an area that is affected by more than three bones at once, "
"e.g. certain areas on a character's face."
msgstr ""
"Peint simultanément sur tous les groupes de sommets, d'une manière qui "
"préserve leur influence relative. Ceci peut être utile dans l'ajustement "
"des poids dans une zone qui est affectée par plus de trois *bones* à la "
"fois, ex. certaines zones du visage d'un personnage."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:89
msgid ""
"This option is only useful in the Armature tab, where you can select "
"multiple Vertex Groups by selecting multiple Pose bones. Once at least "
"two Vertex Groups are selected, viewport colors and paint logic switch to"
" Multi-Paint Mode, using the sum of the selected groups' weights if Auto "
"Normalize is enabled, and the average otherwise. Any paint operations "
"aimed at this collective weight are applied to individual Vertex Group "
"weights in such way that their ratio stays the same."
msgstr ""
"Cette option est seulement utile dans l'onglet *Armature*, où vous pouvez"
" sélectionner plusieurs groupes de sommets en sélectionnant plusieurs "
"*Pose bones*. Une fois qu'au moins deux groupes de sommets sont "
"sélectionnés, les couleurs de la vue et la logique de peinture changent "
"en *Multi-Paint Mode*, en utilisant la somme des poids des groupes "
"sélectionnés si *Auto Normalize* est activé, et la moyenne autrement. "
"Toutes les opérations de peinture visant ce poids collectif sont "
"appliquées aux poids individuels des groupes de sommets de telle manière "
"que leur rapport reste le même."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:95
msgid ""
"Since the ratio is undefined if all weights are zero, Multi-Paint cannot "
"operate on vertices that do not have any weight assigned to the relevant "
"Vertex Groups. For this reason it also does not allow reducing the weight"
" all the way to zero. When used with X Mirror, it only guarantees "
"completely a symmetrical result if weights are initially symmetrical."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:102
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"While Multi-Paint cannot directly paint on zero-weight vertices, it is "
"possible to use the *Smooth Weight* tool to copy a reasonable non-zero "
"weight distribution from adjacent vertices without leaving Multi-Paint "
"Mode or changing bone selection."
msgstr ""
"Bien que *Multi-Paint* ne puisse pas directement peindre sur les sommets "
"de poids nul, il est possible d'utiliser l'outil *Smooth Weight* pour "
"copier une distribution de poids non nul acceptable à partir de sommets "
"adjacents sans quitter le *Multi-Paint Mode* ou changer de sélection "
"d'os."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:106
msgid ""
"To do that, enable vertex selection, select target vertices, and apply "
"one iteration of the tool using vertex groups from *Selected Pose Bones* "
"with low Factor. After that simply paint on top to set the desired "
"collective weight."
msgstr ""
"Pour ce faire, activez la sélection de sommet, sélectionnez les sommets "
"cibles, et appliquez une itération de l'outil utilisant les groupes de "
"sommets de *Selected Pose Bones* avec un facteur bas. Après cela, peignez"
" simplement dessus pour fixer le poids collectif désiré."

